node.text:
While the past few months have been tough for us all, it’s important to remember there’s still good being done in our community. To highlight some of the amazing work being done in Miami, I paid a visit to @joshuasheart on behalf of @jiffylubeintl and Do More to learn all about how Mrs. Mona Lissa Emeran is using her vehicle to give back.
Do More celebrates people who are serving their community through use of their cars — twice a week, Mona Lissa collects fresh bread and pastries from local bakeries to add to Joshua’s Heart meal deliveries, in hopes of giving recipients a wholesome meal and sense of normalcy during these times. On behalf of Jiffy Lube, I was honored to recognize Mona Lissa’s efforts with a year’s worth of free vehicle maintenance services to keep her on the road and helping the community!
Take a look and see why she’s driving to do more, what inspired this amazing selfless act, and the difference it’s making in so many lives. To learn more about Do More or how you can get involved, click the link in my bio or visit JiffyLube.com/DoMore. #Drive2DoMore

node.title: Jiffy Lube International x Do More x Joshua’s Heart Foundation

node.text:
Amazing Grace. I thank the Good Lord every day for the opportunity to serve, create, entertain, and nourish our guests. It’s a blessing I don’t take for granted - not even a single second. I share this award with my Corporate Executive Chef Egg who shares the same, delicious vision  and passion for culinary arts. Thank you for being on this journey with me (almost 15 years 😱) and withstanding the hardships and struggles that come with our industry. We opened not just one, but three restaurants during a global pandemic; I am so proud of what we’ve done and I couldn’t do this without you. To our Executive Chef of Chef Adrianne’s, Chef Nicole, a decade of cooking together has gone by so fast. You are the transporter of Maximum Flavor. Thank you for your diligence, perseverance, and willingness to stay the path even when it was hard to. I am also beyond grateful for our Corporate Brand Manager, Bruce, who’s been known to jump on the hotline when needed, decorate entire dining rooms, and run payroll simultaneously all while making us smile. And to our wonderful guests, who write me #loveletterstoachef , who create memories with us, and allow us the privilege to feed them. A special thank you goes to those who are rooting for us, cheer us on, support us knowing we are pushing forward against all odds in an extremely difficult industry in the most trying of times. 
While some take time out of their day to write on consumer review sites “she grew too fast” “she doesn’t care anymore” “it’s just a chain restaurant now” “she lost it all” “it’s not the same, it will never be the same” ; my heart is exploding with joy because it’s you (our guests) that voted for me. The ones that get it, that have followed along for almost 15 years, and can imagine how difficult the industry really is. Please know that we want to grow because we are simply obsessed with serving you and absolutely love feeding you. Thank you, thank you, and thank you. 

Your friend,
Adri

Impact: To have a strong effect on someone or something.

Grateful to have been part of Impact Week! I had a blast teaching middle school students on their first day of school the importance of eating healthy! 

#makeitcount

node.text:
Join us for our next Dark Dining August 30th as we take our guests out for “ a Night at the Vineyard” . We will be celebrating the beginning of the Harvest in Napa Valley! To commemorate this special evening, we are also hosting a Caymus Vineyards Welcome Party with a performance by String Quartet!!!

***tickets available on Linktree in Bio and on our Website
